{{Infobox Judge |name = Arif Iqbal Bhatti |image = |caption = |nationality = [[Pakistani]] |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = 17 October 1997 |death_place = [[Lahore]], Pakistan |order1 = [[Lahore High Court|Justice of the Lahore High Court]] |term_start1 = 1995 |term_end1 = 1997 |appointer1 = |alma_mater= }} '''Arif Iqbal Hussain Bhatti''' (death 17 October 1997) was a Pakistani jurist who was Judge of the [[Lahore High Court]] and was murdered for alleged blasphemy in verdict.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ucanews.com/story-archive/?post_name=/1997/10/15/pakistani-judge-who-acquitted-christians-of-blasphemy-is-murdered&post_id=10265|title=pakistani judge who acquitted christians of blasphemy is murdered - ucanews.com|publisher=}}</ref>
In 1995, he along Justice Khurshid Ahmed acquitted two Christian men of blasphemy charges.<ref name="tribune.com.pk">{{cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/472495/1990s-blasphemy-acquittal-judges-murder-case-put-in-hibernation/|title=1990s blasphemy acquittal: Judge’s murder case put in ‘hibernation’ - The Express Tribune|date=29 November 2012|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/589587|title=High-profile blasphemy cases in the last 63 years|first=|last=Dawn.com|date=8 December 2010|publisher=}}</ref>
In 1997, he was murdered by the [[Barelvi]] mobster Ahmed Sher for alleged blasphemy by acquitting blasphemy offenders.<ref name="tribune.com.pk"/>
